# Phase 5 constrained MoE offload: GLM-4.5-Air IQ4_XS via mainline llama.cpp.
#
# Strategy: keep MoE expert tensors on CPU (the bulk of weights), offload all
# attention/embedding/output layers to the two 3090s. Selected by `-ot` regex.
# This is the standard "selective expert offload" recipe; it lets us run a
# 106B-A12B MoE that won't fit in VRAM at all.
#
# Memory accounting (approx, IQ4_XS, ~60.81 GB total weights):
#   - MoE expert tensors (FFN ".ffn_.*_exps."): ~50 GB -> CPU RAM
#   - Attention + embed + shared FFN: ~10-12 GB -> split GPU0+GPU1
#   - KV cache @ 16K context: ~2-3 GB -> GPU
# Headroom: still ~10 GB free per GPU for batch/prefill scratch.
#
# Caveats:
# - This is NOT an interactive route. Decode tok/s will be limited by CPU
#   memory bandwidth (~50-80 GB/s on this DDR4 box) and PCIe expert lookup.
#   Expect ~6-12 tok/s, not the 150+ we get from fully-VRAM models.
# - 16K context cap is a budget choice, not a model limit (GLM-4.5-Air can
#   do 128K natively). Increase if RAM headroom allows after first run.

LAB_NAME=llamacpp-glm45air-iq4xs
LAB_IMAGE=ghcr.io/ggml-org/llama.cpp:server-cuda
LAB_GPUS=all
LAB_PORT=8013
LAB_API_KEY=lab-llamacpp-glm45air
LAB_MODEL_PATH=/mnt/data/models/gguf/glm-4.5-air-iq4xs/zai-org_GLM-4.5-Air-IQ4_XS/zai-org_GLM-4.5-Air-IQ4_XS-00001-of-00002.gguf
LAB_SERVED_NAME=lab-glm45air-iq4xs

LAB_ENV_VARS=""

# -ot ".ffn_.*_exps.=CPU"   keep MoE expert tensors on CPU
# -ngl 999                   offload everything else to GPU
# -ts 1,1                    split shared/attention layers 50/50 across GPUs
# -fa on                     flash attention
# --jinja                    use the model's bundled chat template
# -c 16384                   16K context (single slot)
# --parallel 1               single slot to give the one user the full ctx
# --threads 12               match physical cores; tune later if needed
# --no-mlock                 SSD-backed mmap is fine; don't pin all RAM
LAB_LLAMACPP_ARGS="\
  -ngl 999 \
  -ts 1,1 \
  -ot .ffn_.*_exps.=CPU \
  -fa on \
  --jinja \
  -c 16384 \
  --parallel 1 \
  --threads 12 \
  --metrics"
